"\n"
"Our House helms (and in light armor, hoods) cover the entire head, with a "
"full face visor for protection against environmental dangers no matter where "
"our trading takes us. They are of bonemold, or metal crafted to resemble it, "
"bulbous in shape, and elongated toward the back of the skull to protect the "
"traditional cranial coin stash. \n"
"\n"
